Advantages :
        Decrease expenses
        Scale
        Efficiency

The operating system installed in a virtual machine is known as a guest OS, 
as opposed to the host OS on which the virtualization engine is running

Virtualization engine types :
        Hypervisors : 
                Type 1 Hypervisors :
                        Directly create a lightweight operating system on top of the hardware that is the hypervisor
                Type 2 Hypervisors :
                        Add a hypervisor as an application on top of a pre-existing operating system
                        ( VMware Workstation, VMware Fusion, VirtualBox, Parallels, and QEMU )
        Containers
        





